<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN326">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>ūrmutu vēlip pārnaṭai veruki</l>
<l>ṉiruṭpakai verīiya nākiḷam pēṭai</l>
<l>yuyirnaṭuk kuṟṟup pulāviṭ ṭaraṟṟac</l>
<l>ciṟaiyuñ ceṟṟaiyum puṭaiyuna ḷeḻunta</l>
<l>paruttip peṇṭiṉ ciṟutī viḷakkattuk</l>
<l>kavirppū neṟṟic cēvaliṟ ṟaṇiyu</l>
<l>marumiḷai yirukkai yatuvē maṉaiviyum</l>
<l>vēṭṭac ciṟāar cēṭpulam paṭarātu</l>
<l>paṭamaṭaik koṇṭa kuṟuntā ḷuṭumpiṉ</l>
<l>viḻukkuniṇam peyta tayirkkaṇ vitavai</l>
<l>yāṇar nallavai pāṇarō ṭorāṅku</l>
<l>varuvirun tayarum viruppiṉaḷ kiḻavaṉu</l>
<l>maruñcaman tataiyat tākkip peruñcamat</l>
<l>taṇṇal yāṉai yaṇinta</l>
<l>poṉce yōṭaip perumpari cilaṉē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>The village is a seat with a fence difficult [to cross],</l>
<l>where the young hen(?) who is frightened by the enemy of the darkness,</l>
<l>the wild cat on a look-out walk by the old fence,</l>
<l>so that it, trembling for [its] life [and] letting go of [is piece of] flesh, wails,</l>
<l>is calmed down by the rooster with a coral-flower crest</l>
<l>in the lamp with a little fire of the cotton [plucking?] woman</l>
<l>who rises to thrash the side and the bushes.</l>
<l rend="indent8">	The house wife </l>
<l>has a desire for preparing for guests coming</l>
<l>as one with bards the good things freshly available</l>
<l>with gruel on curd poured over the fat pieces</l>
<l>of the short-legged iguana taken by the ? sluice</l>
<l>without setting out of distant fields by the hunting boys,</l>
<l rend="indent14"> and [her] husband</l>
<l>is one for large gifts of gold-made badges</l>
<l>that adorned the majestic elephant</l>
<l>in a great battle after attacking so that the difficult battle was tightly packed.</l>
</lg>
    </div>
